According to iTunes guidelines, in an album, the same primary artist cannot be featured on another
track, and likewise, a featuring artist on one track cannot be a primary artist for another track.
Main artist as featuring for another track within an album
Artist ‘Prophit’ credited as

featuring on track 2 -
Incorrect
6.3. Censoring Words - Use album and track titles as the artist intended them. Explicit words get censored
automatically on Apple Music and iTunes (e.g., F**k or S**t). Don't add asterisks. Self-censorship makes it harder for
listeners to find the content they want.
Censoring in title
Acceptable Example Unacceptable Examples-
The artist's name can be included in the album or track title if it's logical, like "Sir James Top 10 hit songs ever"
(with the main artist's name as 'Sir James Thomas'). However, a title like 'Sir James Thomas - Top 10 hit songs'
would not be acceptable.
Additionally, album titles can be the same as the artist's name, known as a self-titled album.
Artist name in title / Self-titled releases :
iTunes Connect - Common Featuring artist:
Common Featuring –iTunes Connect is a web-based tool that allows you to manage your
deliveries to Apple Music and the iTunes Store. As a distributor, we make use of this tool to make
any metadata updates directly into the stores that our tool currently does not allow/support, such
as: Featured artist credits at album level.
After approval, albums with common featuring artists for all tracks need to be forwarded to the
supervisor. They will update the iTunes Connect backend, manually assigning the featuring artist
at the album level, as our tool doesn't support this feature. Failure to do so may result in Apple
sending feedback. Please exercise caution in such cases.
Common featuring artist on album –Example!
Common Featuring artist
credited on the album title
(done manually thorugh
iTunes Connect)
For albums with fewer than 5 artists and not meeting the 'Various Artist' criteria (which requires five or more Primary artists), set
the Main artist at the album level to "Various Artist." Each individual artist should be credited at the track level. After approval,
these releases are sent to Supervisors, similar to common featuring artist scenarios. The artists will be manually credited at the
album level using the iTunes Connect Application.
